==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Prussic
<hw>Prus"sic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>prussique</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Old Chem.)</fld> <def>designating the
acid now called hydrocyanic acid, but formerly called <xex>prussic
acid</xex>, because Prussian blue is derived from it or its compounds.
See <er>Hydrocyanic</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

